<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-47-1094 </DOCNO><TEXT>C-I-L Ltd., wanting to improve efficiency in its Sarnia Ammonia I plant,decided to use the tracer technique offered by Tracerco Corp. to studysteam flow in the main turbine. Using the pulse velocity method involvingthe injection of a sharp pulse of krypton 85 at selected points in theprocess stream the company obtained data that allowed it to optimizethe turbine. Savings of $520 000. per year have been obtained at a costof $1.1 million. Further data obtained from the tracer shots enabledthe C-I-L team to make some minor corrections to natural gas meteringand storage tank instruments as well.</TEXT></DOC>